uch written detail","Waiting for more information than you need","Using a clear plan before acting"],"correctIndex":0},{"questionId":"ch05-h-q06","prompt":"What is the chapter’s view of trust and reputation?","choices":["They matter only after formal power is secured","They are mostly cosmetic compared with raw force","They are cumulative assets that can be damaged by careless short term wins","They can be repaired instantly with stronger messaging"],"correctIndex":2},{"questionId":"ch05-h-q07","prompt":"Why does the chapter emphasize second order effects?","choices":["Because future incentives and expectations are shaped by today’s move","Because every action should be delayed","Because only symbolic gestures matter","Because outcomes are mostly random"],"correctIndex":0},{"questionId":"ch05-h-q08","prompt":"What ethical line does the chapter try to maintain?","choices":["That strategic awareness should still preserve legitimacy rather than reward empty manipulation","That power always justifies the method","That conflict is resolved best by hiding intentions completely","That fairness matters only when you are already winning"],"correctIndex":0},{"questionId":"ch05-h-q09","prompt":"If someone wanted to apply this chapter in school or work, what habit would fit the summary best?","choices":["Making louder arguments before understanding incentives","Defining the goal, reading the signals, and choosing a proportionate move","Avoiding any decision until conditions are perfect","Copying a tactic without checking the context"],"correctIndex":1},{"questionId":"ch05-h-q10","prompt":"What is the deepest lesson of the chapter for someone in their twenties?","choices":["That pressure should push you to look stronger than you feel","That good judgment comes from reading structure, managing tradeoffs, and acting with restraint","That relationships matter less than leverage","That success mostly depends on being naturally dominant"],"correctIndex":1}]}},{"chapterId":"ch06-names